quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  106,1,"Since the Quraysh became accustomed,",footnotes:182851:1
  106,2,"accustomed to the journey of winter and summer,",footnotes:182852:1
  106,3,"therefore, let them worship the Lord of this House;",footnotes:182853:1
  106,4,"Who fed them against hunger, and secured them against fear.",footnotes:182854:1,footnotes:182855:2
  107,1,"Did you see him who gives the lie to the Reward and Punishment of the Hereafter?",footnotes:182856:1,footnotes:182857:2,footnotes:182858:3
  107,2,"Such is the one who repulses the orphans away,",footnotes:182859:1,footnotes:182860:2
  107,3,"and urges not the feeding of the needy.",footnotes:182861:1,footnotes:182862:2
  107,4,"Woe, then, to those who pray,",footnotes:182863:1
  107,5,"but are heedless in their Prayers,",footnotes:182864:1
  107,6,"those who do good (in order) to be seen,",footnotes:182865:1
  107,7,"and deny people the articles of common necessity.",footnotes:182866:1
  108,1,"(O Prophet), We have surely bestowed upon you good in abundance.",footnotes:182867:1
  108,2,"So offer Prayer and sacrifice to your Lord alone.",footnotes:182868:1
  108,3,"Verily your enemy alone has been cut off from the roots.",footnotes:182869:1,footnotes:182870:2